    • Method Detail

      • detachLinks

        protected void detachLinks()
        Because a RoleGroup is a Container not only the Relations connected to this RoleGroup must be detached/deleted the Relations connected to the children and their children of this RoleGroup must be detached/deleted as well. For that reason the first thing, which is done in this method is to gather all children and their children of this RoleGroup in a single list. After that the Relations connected to children are added to relations list. Detach/Delete all Relations from this Node and their source/target Node and storing the connection information in local data structures.
        Overrides:
        detachLinks in class ORMNodeDeleteCommand
